{"session_id": "497f42c2-3ad7-4077-9a85-40bbbb2bf704", "task": "This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user wants to fix QuickGridView's scroll position jumping to the top/first page when resizing the window width while in **continuous scroll mode** with Grid View open. The user explicitly stated this should only affect continuous scroll mode and should NOT cause regressions in other modes (e.g., non-continuous scroll zoom behavior). The user also requested running simplify, review-loop(codex), patch-claudemd, and commit as a task list.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **QuickGridView**: NSCollectionView overlay toggled by G key, with grid-local thumbnail cache\n   - **gridFrameDidChange**: Notification handler for `NSView.frameDidChangeNotification` on `gridScrollView`, fires during window resize\n   - **Column count changes**: When window width crosses column thresholds, items move to completely different rows in the grid\n   - **Cascading scroll drift**: Each column change moves the anchor item, and the corrupted scroll position becomes the next frame's baseline, cascading to top\n   - **wantsVerticalScroller.didSet**: Calls `tile()` + `reflectScrolledClipView(contentView)` synchronously, which corrupts scroll position before restoration code runs\n   - **cachedVisibleCenter**: Updated at 20Hz by scroll handler, becomes stale during resize because NSScrollView adjusts clip bounds before gridFrameDidChange fires\n   - **ContinuousScrollContentView.relayoutSlots()**: Similar anchor-based preservation pattern that works, but grid's uniform-cell layout behaves differently when columns change\n   - **Live resize session**: Need to capture baseline once and reuse throughout the entire drag, not per-frame\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n   - **`Cee/Views/QuickGridView.swift`** \u2014 Main file being modified\n     - `gridFrameDidChange` (line ~893): The resize handler - originally had NO sc", "stage": "apply", "user_decision": "approve", "edit_distance": 0.004385964912280715, "user_feedback_text": "", "change_type": "docs", "turn_number": 1186, "_swechat_pushback": null, "_swechat_persona": "expert_nitpicker", "_swechat_mode": "vibe", "_swechat_intent": null, "_swechat_success": "28.0", "_swechat_agent_pct": 99.56140350877193}
